article.description: — Jalen Slawson had 16 points and 10 rebounds to carry Furman to an 81-64 victory over Radford in nonconference action Friday night.
article.headline: Slawson powers Furman to 81-64 victory over Radford
article.linkText: Slawson powers Furman to 81-64 victory over Radford
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- — Jalen Slawson had 16 points and 10 rebounds to carry Furman to an 81-64 victory over Radford in nonconference action Friday night. Mike Bothwell contributed 15 points and six assists for the Paladins (3-1). Conley Garrison scored 14, Garrett Hien had 11 points and five assists. Alex Hunter, who was second on the Paladins in scoring averaging 18 points per game, missed all 10 of his shots and scored eight. Shaquan Jules had 12 points for the Highlanders (1-3). Chyree Walker added nine rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
